    "It is also reported that DistMult outperforms TransE with a top-10 accuracy of 73.2% versus 54.7%.TransE: Antoine et al. [80] addressed the problem of embedding different class entities (e.g., metabolites, proteins, etc.)",
    "and relationships of multi-relational data in low-dimensional latent spaces.",
    "The primary condition is that all the different entities (e.g., protein, metabolite, gene, etc.)",
    "must be present in a directed graph.",
    "In this directed graph, a triple fact consists of one entity (designated head), which is related to another entity (designated tail) by an edge (designated label)."
